other_tests.findings: The gallbladder is markedly distended with an impacted stone at the neck, multiple additional stones, large amount of layering sludge, diffuse gallbladder wall edema measuring up to 7 mm, and a small amount of pericholecystic fluid. The liver is normal in echogenicity, mild intrahepatic biliary dilation, and an incidental simple cyst in the right upper renal pole.
